---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const h2 = 'mt-[40px] mb-[12px] text-[24px] font-extrabold tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink';
const p = 'mt-[12px] text-[16.5px] leading-[1.7] text-[#5e574f]';
const li = 'text-[16.5px] leading-[1.7] text-[#5e574f]';
const link = 'text-rust underline underline-offset-2';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Trackie"
  description="How Trackie collects, uses and protects your data. No ads, no tracking, no data sale - and no plaintext email stored."
>
  <article
    class="mt-[8px] rounded-[30px] border border-[rgba(43,39,36,0.07)] bg-white px-[28px] py-[48px] sm:px-[64px] sm:py-[64px]"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[760px]">
      <h1 class="m-0 text-[40px] leading-[1.05] font-extrabold tracking-[-0.025em] text-ink">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-[14px] text-[15px] text-muted-2">Last updated: 22 June 2026</p>

      <p class={p}>
        Trackie (<a href="https://trackie.nz" class={link}>trackie.nz</a>) is a free,
        privacy-focused budgeting service for New Zealand, run by Alan Grainger and
        built on the open-source <a href="https://actualbudget.org" class={link}
          >Actual Budget</a
        >. This policy explains what data Trackie handles, why, and the control you
        have over it. The short version: no ads, no tracking, no data sale - and your
        email is never stored in a form anyone can read.
      </p>

      <h2 class={h2}>What we collect</h2>
      <ul class="mt-[12px] list-disc space-y-[10px] pl-[22px]">
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">Your email, for login only.</strong> Sign
          in is handled by a specialist identity provider over OpenID Connect. We never
          receive or store your password. Your email is stored only as an irreversible
          <code class="rounded bg-rust-soft px-[5px] py-[1px] text-[14px]">HMAC-SHA256</code>
          token - no column in the budget database holds a recoverable email or name. This is
          enforced by automated tests, not just promised here.
        </li>
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">Your budget data.</strong> The categories,
          transactions and notes you enter. This is yours alone; no other user can see it.
          You can optionally <strong class="font-bold">encrypt your budget data with a
          password</strong>, which means not even the server can read it.
        </li>
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">An optional bank connection.</strong> If
          you choose to connect an NZ bank through <a href="https://akahu.nz" class={link}
            >Akahu</a
          >, that access is <strong class="font-bold">read-only</strong> and
          per-user, and the resulting token is encrypted at rest. Trackie can see your
          transactions to help you budget, but it can never move your money. Bank sync is
          entirely optional - importing a statement by hand is a fully supported way to
          use Trackie.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class={h2}>What we don't do</h2>
      <p class={p}>
        No ads. No analytics, tracking or telemetry. We do not sell, rent or mine your
        financial data - ever. There is no third-party advertising or behavioural
        tracking anywhere on the service.
      </p>

      <h2 class={h2}>Where your data lives</h2>
      <p class={p}>
        Access is restricted to New Zealand and served only over HTTPS. Each user's
        budget and any bank connection are isolated to that user. Login is delegated to a
        self-hosted identity provider, so passwords never reach the budgeting service.
      </p>

      <h2 class={h2}>Your control</h2>
      <ul class="mt-[12px] list-disc space-y-[10px] pl-[22px]">
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">Export any time.</strong> You can export your
          full budget whenever you like. There is no lock-in.
        </li>
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">Disconnect any time.</strong> Any bank
          connection can be switched off whenever you choose.
        </li>
        <li class={li}>
          <strong class="font-bold text-ink">Delete your account.</strong> Removing your
          account removes your budget files and, by cascade, any Akahu connection. Dormant
          or empty accounts may be cleaned up periodically as part of storage and abuse
          management.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class={h2}>Transparency</h2>
      <p class={p}>
        The exact code that runs this service is <a
          href="https://github.com/alangrainger/trackie"
          class={link}>public on GitHub</a
        >. The entire difference from upstream Actual Budget is published and
        intentionally small, so anyone can confirm precisely what handles your data.
      </p>

      <h2 class={h2}>Contact</h2>
      <p class={p}>
        Questions about your privacy, or want to report a security issue? See the
        <a href="https://github.com/alangrainger/trackie/blob/main/SECURITY.md" class={link}
          >security policy</a
        > on GitHub, or get in touch with <a
          href="https://github.com/alangrainger"
          class={link}>Alan Grainger</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
